        <div class="section-label">Our Philosophy</div>
        <h2>The ancient answer to a <em>modern crisis</em></h2>
        <p>We live in the most information-rich era in human history — and yet, for many, authentic self-knowledge feels further away than ever. Algorithms curate our worldview. Screens mediate our relationships. The signal is buried beneath an avalanche of noise.</p>
        <p>Freemasonry offers something rare in the twenty-first century: a deliberate, structured space to slow down, look inward, and stand in genuine community with other seekers.</p>

        <div class="harari-quote">
          <blockquote>"In a world deluged by irrelevant information, clarity is power."</blockquote>
          <cite>— Yuval Noah Harari, 21 Lessons for the 21st Century</cite>
        </div>

        <p>Sharman Crawford Lodge does not claim to have all the answers. We offer something better — a brotherhood of men committed to asking the right questions, together.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillars">
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-number">01</div>
          <h3>Brotherly Love</h3>
          <p>True connection in an age of curated personas. We meet as we are, not as we present ourselves online.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-number">02</div>
          <h3>Relief</h3>
          <p>Active service to our community and to those in need — translating inner work into outward compassion.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-number">03</div>
          <h3>Truth</h3>
